{"title": "Japan primed for tourism windfall, but without big-spending Chinese", "tags": "asia", "timestamp": "2022-09-23", "content": "TOKYO - Japan is primed for a tourism windfall from pent-up demand overseas as, for the first time in 2\u00bd years, it throws open its borders to visa-free individual travellers from Oct 11.\nThe decisive measure, announced by Prime Minister Fumio Kishida in New York on Thursday, comes after months of baby steps that have proven to be head-scratching and cumbersome for potential visitors."}